961, "text": "The brisket was dry, but the sausage and ribs were pretty good. Also, you may want to bring your own barbecue sauce. I've had better barbecue at Cheddars so this place was a bit disappointing.", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Anjuan Simmons"}, {"date": "November 21, 2014", "text": "Brisket, Sausages, chicken...everything....best BBQ in the Houston area!!", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Jan Poepke"}, {"date": 1367352252, "text": "For all the complaints about the pickles...  They charge $0.20 for a plate full.", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 1, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Allen Arcade"}, {"date": 1486348075, "text": "I almost shouted to him, "she thought that was for a whole brisket!" Beef and Bun or Pa's Pa's bbq is 10 X better. For those reasons this place is a 1*", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Mark Brown"}, {"date": 1396140296, "text": "Beef ribs and beef links are a must have", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "We Parlay"}, {"date": 1423683622, "text": "Brisket & sausage are delicious!", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Christina"}, {"date": 1367465717, "text": "Consistently burnt ribs and dry brisket. Don't ever come to this rip-off of City Market in Luling, TX.", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 1, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Redwan Huq"}, {"date": 1452730068, "text": "Barbecue!?", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "?Sun!"}, {"date": 1424895089, "text": "Definately best BBQ in town!!!", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Jan Poepke"}, {"date": 1486348033, "text": "Way over priced, chewy beef and rude serv. 1st and last time customer hit with $73 for 3.5 lbs of ave rated meat an elderly lady asked "why so much"  the server yelled "the price is on the menu mam!"", "source": "fo