pvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Ray Kennedy"}, {"date": 1303255376, "text": "This place has gone down the hill!", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Rahim Tazehzadeh"}, {"date": 1387138601, "text": "Worse barbecue sauce ever. The food was so-so.", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Joe Dotson"}, {"date": 1368125864, "text": "Why are they so rude here? First time and last time here.", "source": "foursquare", "upvotes": 0, "downvotes": 0, "author_name": "Chris Soto"}], "tripadvisor": [{"date": 1510257146, "text": "Stopped by this place late and had dinner. Meats were all very good, but the sides, ie, cole slaw, pinto beans, etc. were just okay. Spicy pickles were very good", "quote": "Good barbecue, sides just okay", "rating": "4", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "L A D", "posted_from_mobile": false, "relative_date_found": "1 week ago"}, {"date": "September 26, 2017", "text": "This briskets is awesome! With coleslaw and some homemade pickles - and the place is so authentic! I would have never gone in if it was not for a business dinner some years ago! Since then I recommend this place to everybody, and everyone came...", "quote": "Best brisket", "rating": "5", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "Regina B", "posted_from_mobile": true, "relative_date_found": "September 26, 2017"}, {"date": "September 16, 2017", "text": "Stopped here for dinner. We ordered link lean brisket juicy brisket potatoes salad and beans. White bread is given with your order. You order by the 1/2 pound or pound. The atmosphere is a bit older and we were the only people eating in the...", "quote": "Good Lean Brisket", "rating": "3", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "Sweetie333", "posted_from_mobile": true, "relative_date_found": "September 16, 2017"}, {"date": 1504076400, "text": "I always visit Luling City Market when I'm in Houston. The brisket and beef sausage is really good. They didn't give me much bark on my brisket last time but it was still good. Staff is very friendly too.", "quote": "Really good BBQ", "rating": "4", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "zwildcats", "posted_from_mobile": false, "relative_date_found": "August 30, 2017"}, {"date": 1503126000, "text": "Hole in the wall authentic BBQ. Best brisket I've had. Good portion size. Baked beans were delicious.", "quote": "Best brisket", "rating": "5", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "SeafoodSnob", "posted_from_mobile": true, "relative_date_found": "August 19, 2017"}, {"date": 1502780400, "text": "Met a group here for dinner. I am from out of town and was told by the locals this was THE place for BBQ in Houston. Well the Brisket was good but lacked flavor of smoke. The sides were minimal. For me, just a miss...", "quote": "Not as good as Hyped", "rating": "3", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "Grizbaer", "posted_from_mobile": false, "relative_date_found": "August 15, 2017"}, {"date": 1501052400, "text": "Kurtz and his team are spot on when it comes to Texan BBQ. Great place, friendly atmosphere and top notch food. This is the place to go for the real Houston.", "quote": "The real deal", "rating": "5", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "craigbrown2017", "posted_from_mobile": false, "relative_date_found": "July 26, 2017"}, {"date": 1500015600, "text": "When I walked in the door of this unassuming establishment I weld that it was absolutely, genuinely about the food and great barbecued brisket, ribs and chicken. The meat was cooked beautifully and is sold by the pound. No need for plates here, the meat...", "quote": "Authentic barbecue.", "rating": "5", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "ZanderAustralia", "posted_from_mobile": true, "relative_date_found": "July 14, 2017"}, {"date": 1499842800, "text": "Just OK. Brisket was overly greasy, beans lacked flavor as dis potato salad. I won't return. I still want to try the original restaurant in Luling, which is always packed.", "quote": "First Time", "rating": "4", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "parpaced", "posted_from_mobile": true, "relative_date_found": "July 12, 2017"}, {"date": 1499410800, "text": "I took a work colleague to Luling. He's from the Midwest and was in town for business. He immediately loved the vibe in the restaurant. I had an excellent turkey and sausage combo with potato salad. He had brisket and sausage and while eating it...", "quote": "My Colleague Said Best Sausage Ever Tasted", "rating": "5", "source": "tripadvisor", "author_name": "Kevin W", "posted_from_mobile": false, "relative_date_found": "July 7, 2017"}], "yellowpages": [{"date": "September 14, 2015", "text": "Iys pretty good, depends what you get", "title": "", "rating": 3, "source": "yellowpages", "author_name": "Barry G."}, {"date": "September 13, 2010", "text": "This place has some real Texas barbecue and it's delicious.  The chopped beef sandwich is the best I've had.", "title": "Great Barbecue", "rating": 5, "source": "yellowpages", "author_name": "Nicholas P."}, {"date": "November 27, 2007", "text": "While the BBQ is incredible and I love the sauce. The smoke ring and great flavor is available elsewhere.  Like Goode co. the problem with Luling City Market is the lack of service and hostile employees.  Why bother to eat at place that would rather cheat than feed you.  I think Houston BBQ on Elderidge is better and they don't make up the number for what it will cost. I will never go back.", "title": "Once great - Luling City Market fails today", "rating": 1, "source": "yellowpages", "author_name": "winglow"}], "googleplaces": [{"text": "Best BBQ in Houston.  Most unique sausage I have ever had. Brisket is great.  Sauce is the best!!", "rating": 5, "source": "googleplaces", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109881239841299597585/reviews", "author_name": "James Spears"}, {"text": "OMG!  Not greasy!  Everything my husband and I had was mouth watering delicious.  Had us wanting more the next day.", "rating": 5, "source": "googleplaces", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112859436617230738082/reviews", "author_name": "KVKClay Family"}, {"text": "Extremely good barbecue. Really enjoyed the laid-back atmosphere and great service. It was nice to have barbeque that's not like everybody else.", "rating": 4, "source": "googleplaces", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111415355791013291971/reviews", "author_name": "Greg Sanderson"}, {"text": "Best BBQ in town. Brisket/ribs are excellent. Sausage is phenomenal", "rating": 5, "source": "googleplaces", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100807491604494018419/reviews", "author_name": "nick cagle"}, {"text": "If you know anything about Texas BBQ, this is the real deal.  Brisket and ribs, served by the pound - "yeh, cut me off a couple more slices of that brisket!"

Wonderful service and true Texas BBQ ambience.  This is no "chain".  Bring your friends, bring your visitors (hell, bring your cousin).  

I'll be back!", "rating": 5, "source": "googleplaces", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104572060627876558041/reviews", "author_name": "Kevin Gantz"}]}}

